{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "02", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "13", "M": "25", "S": "45"}}, "news": [{"title": "Nine of 10 buildings fail fire safety checks across Nagpur's fire stations", "para": "Nagpur's fire safety compliance is alarmingly low, with over 90% of inspected buildings in some areas violating norms. RTI data reveals widespread non-compliance across multiple fire station jurisdictions, despite regular inspections. While the fire department efficiently processes No Objection Certificates and reports no fire-related deaths, the high violation rate highlights significant enforcement gaps. This stark contrast demands immediate attention to ensure public safety.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/over-90-of-buildings-fail-fire-safety-norms-in-nagpur-shocking-statistics-revealed/132134139?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-518482/132134139.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Telangana government forms committee to probe Dharani, Bhu Bharathi irregularities", "para": "The Telangana government has formed a special committee to investigate irregularities in the Dharani and Bhu Bharathi land portals. Following the identification of security flaws and unauthorized entries, the committee will identify those responsible, take stringent action, and propose preventive measures. The National Informatics Centre has been tasked with developing a new, secure system architecture.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/technology/telangana-government-launches-investigation-into-dharani-and-bhu-bharathi-portal-irregularities/132134166?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-651756/132134166.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "technology"}, {"title": "Panchkula collects just \u20b95.9 crore of target \u20b9100 crore property tax", "para": "Panchkula MC has collected a mere \u20b95.9 crore from over \u20b9100 crore in outstanding property tax, even after a 100% interest waiver. Major defaulters, owing \u20b940 crore, are now facing stricter measures. The municipal commissioner has ordered priority identification and issuance of rules-based notices, with legal action and property sealing as potential next steps to bolster the corporation's finances and civic service delivery.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/panchkulas-struggle-to-collect-property-tax-only-59-crore-collected-of-100-crore-target-amid-waiver-scheme/132134116?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-222996/132134116.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}